descriptions: Processed development proposals and other administrative documents, ensuring compliance with internal procedures and relevant legislation, while maintaining strong verbal communication and customer service with ministry staff.
Applied organizational and time-management skills to prioritize and coordinate office tasks, ensuring competing deadlines were met in a dynamic environment.
Demonstrated proficiency in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint), using these tools to prepare reports, update files, and manage electronic records, ensuring data accuracy and integrity.
Streamlined clinic operations, improving efficiency and workflow while mentoring new staff and ensuring adherence to healthcare policies and procedures.
Fostered strong relationships with both internal healthcare teams and external stakeholders, ensuring clear communication and effective solutions for patient care.
Developed and implemented innovative strategies to optimize clinic performance, consistently surpassing patient service and appointment scheduling targets.
